        <Relationship_Type>Parent/Child</Relationship_Type>
        <Historic_Flag>Current</Historic_Flag>
        <Parent_String>screens in Christian religious buildings [300265151], Christian religious building fixtures [300003724], religious building fixtures [300003723], architectural elements by building type [300078071], architectural elements [300000885], components by specific context [300241584], components (objects parts) [300241583], Components (hierarchy name) [300241490], Objects Facet [300264092]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to screens in Christian churches that separate the choir from the nave and aisles of a church. For partitions that separate the chancel from the nave of the church, use "chancel screens." For partitions that separate the altar from the choir, use "reredos."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Verwijst naar afsluitingen in christelijke kerken waarmee het koor wordt afgescheiden van het schip en de zijbeuken van een kerk. Gebruik 'koorschermen' voor afsluitingen waarmee het koor wordt gescheiden van het schip van de kerk. Gebruik 'reredoses' voor afsluitingen waarmee het altaar wordt gescheiden van het koor.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099099/Van Dale groot woordenboek (1994)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>基督教教堂中，將唱詩班席與中堂及走道隔開的圍屏。劃分聖壇和教堂中堂的分隔物，以「聖壇圍屏 (chancel screens)」稱之。至於祭壇和唱詩班席之間的分隔物，則以「祭壇背壁（reredos）」稱之。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
